FluxCD integrates directly with Kubernetes health checks to prevent a broken container from taking down live traffic:

    Health Assessment: You configure health checks in your Flux Kustomization manifest:


    apiVersion: kustomize.toolkit.fluxcd.io/v1
kind: Kustomization
metadata:
  name: apps
  namespace: flux-system
spec:
  interval: 5m
  path: ./apps
  prune: true
  wait: true             # Instructs Flux to wait for resources to become Ready
  timeout: 2m            # Max time to wait before marking the deployment as failed


  What happens on failure:

   - If a new image contains a bug 

   - The existing healthy pods continue serving traffic (zero downtime).

  -  FluxCD’s kustomize-controller times out after 2m, marks the GitOps reconciliation status as Failed
